10 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
11 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
12 Article – Economic Development
13 SUBTITLE 12. PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY SUITLAND DEVELOPMENT AUTHORITY.
14 12–1201.
15 (A) IN THIS SUBTITLE THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
16 INDICATED.
17 (B) “AUTHORITY” MEANS THE SUITLAND DEVELOPMENT AUTHORITY.
18 (C) “BOARD” MEANS THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS OF THE AUTHORITY.
19 (D) “BUFFER ZONE” MEANS THE AREA WITHIN 250 YARDS OF THE TARGET
20 AREA.
21 (E) “TARGET AREA” MEANS THE SUITLAND ROAD AND SILVER HILL ROAD
22 CORRIDOR IN PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY.
23 12–1202.
24 THIS SUBTITLE SHALL BE LIBERALLY CONSTRUED TO ACCOMPLISH ITS
25 PURPOSES.
26 12–1203.
27 (A) THERE IS A SUITLAND DEVELOPMENT AUTHORITY IN PRINCE
28 GEORGE’S COUNTY.

SENATE BILL 552 3
1 (B) THE AUTHORITY IS A BODY POLITIC AND CORPORATE AND IS AN
2 INSTRUMENTALITY OF THE STATE.
3 (C) THE EXERCISE BY THE AUTHORITY OF A POWER UNDER THIS SUBTITLE
4 IS THE PERFORMANCE OF AN ESSENTIAL GOVERNMENTAL FUNCTION.
5 (D) THE GOVERNOR MAY SHALL INCLUDE EACH YEAR IN THE STATE
6 ANNUAL BUDGET BILL AN APPROPRIATION OF $500,000 TO THE AUTHORITY IN
7 PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY.
8 (E) BEGINNING FISCAL YEAR 2036, THE AUTHORITY SHALL BE
9 SELF–SUSTAINING.
10 12–1204.
11 (A) THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY FINDS THAT:
12 (1) THERE EXISTS WITHIN VARIOUS NEIGHBORHOODS IN PRINCE
13 GEORGE’S COUNTY, PARTICULARLY THE SUITLAND ROAD AND SILVER HILL ROAD
14 CORRIDOR, A NEED FOR RESIDENTIAL AND COMMERCIAL DEVELOPMENT OR
15 REDEVELOPMENT IN FURTHERANCE OF THE PUBLIC’S INTEREST;
16 (2) THE SUITLAND ROAD AND SILVER HILL ROAD CORRIDOR HAS
17 EXPERIENCED LOW HOUSING AND ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT IN THE COMMUNITY
18 FOR DECADES;
19 (3) AREAS IN THE SUITLAND ROAD AND SILVER HILL ROAD
20 CORRIDOR INCLUDE BOTH AREAS THAT ARE CONSIDERED SLUM OR BLIGHTED AND
21 AREAS THAT ARE DETERIORATED OR SUBJECT TO FURTHER DETERIORATING
22 CONDITION, AND THOSE AREAS ARE IN NEED OF DEVELOPMENT OR
23 REDEVELOPMENT FOR THE PUBLIC BENEFIT;
24 (4) THE REVITALIZATION OF AREAS WITHIN THE SUITLAND ROAD
25 AND SILVER HILL ROAD CORRIDOR NEEDING COMMERCIAL DEVELOPMENT OR
26 REDEVELOPMENT IS AN ESSENTIAL GOVERNMENTAL FUNCTION AND IS A PUBLIC
27 USE THAT WILL CONFER A PUBLIC BENEFIT ON CITIZENS OF PRINCE GEORGE’S
28 COUNTY BY:
29 (I) RELIEVING CONDITIONS OF UNEMPLOYMENT;
30 (II) ENCOURAGING THE INCREASE OF COMMERCE AND A
31 BALANCED ECONOMY;

4 SENATE BILL 552
1 (III) ASSISTING IN THE RETENTION OF BUSINESSES AND
2 RESIDENTS;
3 (IV) ATTRACTING NEW INDUSTRIES AND COMMERCE;
4 (V) PROMOTING ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT AND GROWTH; AND
5 (VI) GENERALLY PROMOTING THE HEALTH, WELFARE, AND
6 PUBLIC SAFETY OF RESIDENTS IN PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY AND INCREASING
7 PROPERTY TAX REVENUES FOR THE STATE AND PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY;
8 (5) THE ESTABLISHMENT OF THIS PUBLIC AUTHORITY TO PROVIDE
9 FINANCIAL RESOURCES FOR THE DEVELOPMENT AND ESTABLISHMENT OF
10 RESIDENCES AND BUSINESSES THROUGH COMMUNITY ORGANIZATIONS IN THE
11 TARGET AREA WILL SIGNIFICANTLY IMPROVE PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY
12 NEIGHBORHOODS AND INCREASE PROPERTY TAX REVENUES FOR THE STATE AND
13 PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY; AND
14 (6) THE AUTHORITY IS THE ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT AUTHORITY
15 FOR THE STATE TO BENEFIT THE NEIGHBORHOODS OF PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY
16 WITHIN THE TARGET AREA.
17 (B) THE LEGISLATIVE PURPOSES OF THE AUTHORITY ARE TO:
18 (1) REVIVE THE VARIOUS COMMUNITIES ALONG THE SUITLAND ROAD
19 AND SILVER HILL ROAD CORRIDOR IN PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY;
20 (2) PROMOTE ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT;
21 (3) ENCOURAGE THE INCREASE OF BUSINESS ACTIVITY, COMMERCE,
22 AND A BALANCED ECONOMY IN PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY;
23 (4) HELP TO RETAIN AND ATTRACT BUSINESS ACTIVITY AND
24 COMMERCE IN PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY; AND
25 (5) PROMOTE THE HEALTH, PUBLIC SAFETY, RIGHT OF GAINFUL
26 EMPLOYMENT, AND WELFARE OF RESIDENTS OF PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY.
27 (C) THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY INTENDS THAT:
28 (1) THE AUTHORITY OPERATE AND EXERCISE ITS CORPORATE
29 POWERS ALONG THE SUITLAND ROAD AND SILVER HILL ROAD CORRIDOR IN
30 PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY;

SENATE BILL 552 5
1 (2) WITHOUT LIMITING ITS AUTHORITY TO OTHERWISE EXERCISE ITS
2 POWERS, THE AUTHORITY EXERCISES ITS POWERS TO ASSIST PRIVATE REAL ESTATE
3 ENTITIES AND NONPROFIT COMMUNITY DEVELOPMENT CORPORATIONS TO
4 DEVELOP AND REHABILITATE HOUSING AND COMMERCIAL UNITS IN PRINCE
5 GEORGE’S COUNTY AND SUPPORT LOCAL ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT AGENCIES TO
6 CONTRIBUTE TO THE EXPANSION, MODERNIZATION, AND RETENTION OF EXISTING
7 ENTERPRISES IN PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY AS WELL AS THE ATTRACTION OF NEW
8 BUSINESSES TO PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY; AND
9 (3) THE AUTHORITY SHOULD NOT OWN AND OPERATE A PROJECT
10 UNLESS:
11 (I) THE BOARD DETERMINES BY RESOLUTION THAT THE
12 PRIVATE SECTOR HAS NOT DEMONSTRATED SERIOUS AND SIGNIFICANT INTEREST
13 AND DEVELOPMENT CAPACITY TO OWN AND OPERATE THE PROJECT; OR
14 (II) A REPRESENTATIVE OF A GOVERNMENTAL UNIT REQUESTS
15 IN WRITING THAT THE AUTHORITY OWN AND OPERATE THE PROJECT.
16 12–1205.
17 (A) (1) EXCEPT AS OTHERWISE PROVIDED IN THIS SECTION, IN
18 EXERCISING ITS POWERS, THE AUTHORITY:
19 (I) MAY CARRY OUT THE PURPOSES OF THE AUTHORITY
20 WITHOUT THE CONSENT OF ANY STATE UNIT; AND
21 (II) IS NOT SUBJECT TO:
22 1. SUBTITLES 1 THROUGH 3 OF THIS TITLE; OR
23 2. THE FOLLOWING PROVISIONS OF THE STATE
24 FINANCE AND PROCUREMENT ARTICLE:
25 A. TITLE 2, SUBTITLES 2 (GIFTS AND GRANTS) AND 5
26 (FACILITIES FOR THE HANDICAPPED);
27 B. TITLE 3 (BUDGET AND MANAGEMENT);
28 C. TITLE 4 (DEPARTMENT OF GENERAL SERVICES);

6 SENATE BILL 552
1 D. TITLE 5A (DIVISION OF HISTORICAL AND CULTURAL
2 PROGRAMS);
3 E. TITLE 6, SUBTITLE 1 (STUDIES AND ESTIMATES);
4 F. TITLE 7, SUBTITLES 1 (STATE OPERATING BUDGET),
5 2 (DISBURSEMENTS AND EXPENDITURES), AND 3 (UNSPENT BALANCES);
6 G. TITLE 10 (BOARD OF PUBLIC
7 WORKS – MISCELLANEOUS PROVISIONS); OR
8 H. DIVISION II (GENERAL PROCUREMENT LAW).
9 (2) THE AUTHORITY IS SUBJECT TO:
10 (I) THE PUBLIC INFORMATION ACT; AND
11 (II) THE OPEN MEETINGS ACT.
12 (B) THE AUTHORITY AND ITS OFFICERS AND EMPLOYEES ARE SUBJECT TO
13 THE PUBLIC ETHICS LAW.
14 (C) THE AUTHORITY AND ITS OFFICERS AND EMPLOYEES ARE SUBJECT TO
15 TITLE 12, SUBTITLE 4 OF THE STATE FINANCE AND PROCUREMENT ARTICLE.
16 (D) THE AUTHORITY IS SUBJECT TO TITLE 14, SUBTITLE 3 OF THE STATE
17 FINANCE AND PROCUREMENT ARTICLE.
18 12–1206.
19 (A) A BOARD OF DIRECTORS SHALL MANAGE THE AUTHORITY AND
20 EXERCISE ITS POWERS.
21 (B) THE BOARD CONSISTS OF THE FOLLOWING MEMBERS:
22 (1) ONE MEMBER OF THE SENATE OF MARYLAND WHO REPRESENTS
23 THE TARGET AREA TO SERVE IN AN ADVISORY CAPACITY, APPOINTED BY THE
24 PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE;
25 (2) ONE MEMBER OF THE HOUSE OF DELEGATES WHO REPRESENTS
26 THE TARGET AREA TO SERVE IN AN ADVISORY CAPACITY, APPOINTED BY THE
27 SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE;

