8 SENATE BILL 552
1 (14) (15) ONE SUITLAND COMMUNITY MEMBER, APPOINTED BY THE
2 PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE;
3 (16) ONE SUITLAND COMMUNITY MEMBER, APPOINTED BY THE
4 COUNTY EXECUTIVE OF PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY; AND
5 (15) (17) ONE COMMERCIAL PROPERTY OWNER WITHIN THE TARGET
6 AREA, APPOINTED BY THE COUNTY EXECUTIVE.
7 (C) THE COUNTY EXECUTIVE SHALL SELECT THE CHAIR OF THE BOARD.
8 12–1207.
9 (A) THE AUTHORITY MAY MANAGE APPROPRIATED FUNDS FROM PRINCE
10 GEORGE’S COUNTY AND THE STATE.
11 (B) THE AUTHORITY MAY RECEIVE DONATED SERVICES FROM
12 ACCOUNTANTS, LAWYERS, OR OTHER CONSULTANTS AS NECESSARY TO CARRY OUT
13 THIS SUBTITLE.
14 (C) THE AUTHORITY MAY SUPERVISE, MANAGE, AND TERMINATE STAFF
15 AND CONSULTANTS AS NECESSARY.
16 12–1208.
17 A MEMBER OF THE AUTHORITY:
18 (1) MAY NOT RECEIVE COMPENSATION AS A MEMBER OF THE
19 AUTHORITY; BUT
20 (2) IS ENTITLED TO REIMBURSEMENT FOR EXPENSES UNDER THE
21 STANDARD STATE TRAVEL REGULATIONS, AS PROVIDED IN THE STATE BUDGET.
22 12–1209.
23 (A) THE AUTHORITY SHALL:
24 (1) SUPPORT THE DEVELOPMENT AND APPROVAL OF A
25 COMPREHENSIVE NEIGHBORHOOD REVITALIZATION PLAN IN THE TARGET AREA
26 AND THE BUFFER ZONE TO BENEFIT:
27 (I) THE RESIDENTS;

SENATE BILL 552 9
1 (II) HOUSING;
2 (III) NEIGHBORHOODS;
3 (IV) ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT; AND
4 (V) TRANSPORTATION, INCLUDING MOTOR VEHICLES AND
5 PEDESTRIANS; AND
6 (2) WORK IN COORDINATION WITH THE RESIDENTS OF THE TARGET
7 AREA AND THE BUFFER ZONE TO DEVELOP A COMPREHENSIVE NEIGHBORHOOD
8 REVITALIZATION PLAN.
9 (B) THE AUTHORITY MAY, BY A MAJORITY VOTE OF ALL MEMBERS OF THE
10 AUTHORITY, MODIFY THE BOUNDARIES OF THE TARGET AREA AND THE BUFFER
11 ZONE.
12 (C) ON OR BEFORE DECEMBER 15, 2027, THE AUTHORITY SHALL REPORT
13 ITS COMPREHENSIVE NEIGHBORHOOD REVITALIZATION STRATEGY, INCLUDING ANY
14 PROCUREMENT ACTIVITIES UNDERTAKEN BY THE AUTHORITY, TO THE GOVERNOR
15 AND, IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE, TO
16 THE SENATE BUDGET AND TAXATION COMMITTEE, THE HOUSE ECONOMIC
17 MATTERS COMMITTEE, AND THE HOUSE APPROPRIATIONS COMMITTEE.
18 12–1210.
19 THE AUTHORITY MAY:
20 (1) ADOPT BYLAWS FOR THE CONDUCT OF THE BUSINESS OF THE
21 AUTHORITY;
22 (2) ADOPT A SEAL;
23 (3) SUE OR BE SUED;
24 (4) MAINTAIN AN OFFICE AT A PLACE THE AUTHORITY DESIGNATES
25 IN PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY;
26 (5) MAKE OR ACCEPT AND MANAGE LOANS, GRANTS, OR ASSISTANCE
27 OF ANY KIND FROM THE FEDERAL OR STATE GOVERNMENT, A LOCAL GOVERNMENT,
28 A COLLEGE OR UNIVERSITY, A CHARITABLE INSTITUTION, A NONPROFIT
29 ORGANIZATION, A FOR–PROFIT ORGANIZATION, OR A PRIVATE SOURCE;

10 SENATE BILL 552
1 (6) MAKE GRANTS TO INDIVIDUALS;
2 (7) ACQUIRE PROPERTIES IN PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY, DIRECTLY
