19 12–1211.
20 (A) THE AUTHORITY SHALL ESTABLISH A SYSTEM OF FINANCIAL
21 ACCOUNTING, CONTROLS, AUDITS, AND REPORTS.
22 (B) THE FISCAL YEAR OF THE AUTHORITY BEGINS ON JULY 1 AND ENDS ON
23 THE FOLLOWING JUNE 30.
24 12–1212.
25 (A) THE AUTHORITY MAY CREATE AND ADMINISTER THE ACCOUNTS THAT
26 THE AUTHORITY REQUIRES.
